“ Adducit febres et testamenta resignat.’' (Horace, Ep. i. 7. 9.)

To take the seals off a thing before the time is a fraudulent act. When the seals are off, the thing may be falsified. Cicero means that the condemnationi of Gabinius destroyed his credit, and was the same thing as if you took the scals off a testament or other in- strument and left it open to the falsifier.
